column5: Monica and I just had to get out of the house, so on Saturday we took a trip up to devil's Lake, near Minden. Just enough time for some lure washing and a swim before the clouds looked like they might end the day with a soaking. Nothing big was caught, but we were just glad to get out and relax on the water.
Can't beat a day on the water! Even if its a short one! Looks like you went up just in time! This just happened toÂ the road! Wonder how long of a hike it is?
WOW! Where exactly is that, somewhere on Deep Bay Road, or Devil's Lake Road?
That looks like the Deep Bay Road washout between Gull and Devil's.
Also, beautiful scenery. I've been eyeing this area up for a day trip.
